# PLAYHUB — Core Project Rules

## Stack (mandatory)
- TypeScript, Next.js App Router, Supabase (Auth, DB, Realtime, Storage)
- Tailwind CSS, Shadcn UI, Zod, React Hook Form, Lucide Icons
- Deploy target: Vercel Free + Supabase Free

## Forbidden
- Firebase, Clerk, AWS/Azure/GCP, paid third-party APIs

## Architecture
- Feature-based layout: `src/features/{module}/` (components, hooks, actions)
- Shared UI in `src/components/`; domain logic in `src/lib/domain/`
- Prefer Server Components; use `"use client"` only for interactivity
- No duplicate code — extract reusable components and shared Zod schemas
- Clean architecture + SOLID: single responsibility, depend on abstractions
- Never remove working code; extend and refactor safely

## Data & validation
- Zod schemas in `src/lib/validators/`; share between forms and server actions
- React Hook Form + `@hookform/resolvers/zod` for interactive forms
- RLS is the authorization source of truth; validate on server always

## UI/UX
- Mobile-first, fully responsive, dark mode support (`next-themes` + CSS variables)
- Loading, error, and empty states on all async UI

## Process
- Build module-by-module; never generate the entire app at once
- After each module: update `TASKS.md`, `ROADMAP.md`, `README.md`, and relevant `/docs`
- Explain major architecture decisions in code reviews and docs
- Keep app deployable on Vercel after every module
